# Theme axis audit (mandatory procedure)

When the user asks to:

- audit theme / appearance config compliance
- fix presets not applying across the UI
- continue **"theme axis one by one"** or **"do elevation"** / **"do density"** etc.
- make Shuffle / Appearance settings apply everywhere

**You MUST:**

1. Read **`agent-os/skills/theme-axis-audit/SKILL.md`** first.
2. Read **`docs/reference/theme-axis-audit-playbook.md`** (status tracker + catalog).
3. Work **one axis per cycle** (or a playbook-defined pair).
4. Complete **Phases 0–4** without asking for confirmation.
5. Deliver the **detailed cycle report** (template in the skill).
6. Update the **playbook status tracker** when done.

**Do not** skip grep inventory, index.css slot extensions, or colocated tests.

**Related:** radius/shape already done — use the same patterns (`data-slot`, `<Card>`, remove hardcoded utilities).
